content.description: Move up the easy crack to the 1st of 5 bolts then follow the crack to the top.  At the 3rd bolt you meander left to a ledge or head straight up, the latter adding difficulty to this fun, steep mixed route.
content.protection: 5 bolts and standard rack to a #3.
content.location: This is the leftmost bolted line when you get to the Seitch face.  Anchors at top.  Apx. 100' rap.

climbs.name: Seitch Tactics
climbs.fa: Steve Gerberding, Al Swanson & Cal Gerberding, December 2003

content.description: Climb up over easier rock to get to the first bolt.  Face climb over the bulges and make your way past the crux at the main roof.  After the last bolt, get gear where you can and continue up to the bolted anchor.
content.protection: 6 bolts and a standard rack to a #3.
content.location: Route starts just to the right of The Shiv.  Bolted anchor is to the right of The Shiv's anchor.

content.description: Cool sport route that boasts a techy and then a desperate crux section surmounting the final overlap.
content.location: Starts to the right of Seitch Tactics.  Bolted Anchor.  Rap the route.

content.description:
This short climb is on the far right side of the southwest face.

On the far right of the face are two parallel chimneys that start about two thirds of the way up the rock. The left chimney has a chockstone and a corner leading up to it. This is the route.  Make an entry move up to a small ledge. Climb up the corner crack, passing horizontal cracks, to the alcove beneath the chimney. Continue up the chimney. The chockstone is kinda' scary, it appears to be barely hanging there. I pushed on it and it didn't move, but I didn't use it or step on the top of it.

Walk off the backside.

This starts about ten feet left of "n00b t00b". Climb up face and seams to a ledge. Step left to a right leaning crack with jugs and follow it to the top.

Walk off the backside.
content.protection: Long slings to go around boulders.
